						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near the tank 1(1/2) km South west of the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1726, Raktākshi, Kārttīka śu. 13, Thurday,</hi> corresponding to 1804 A.D., November 15.</p>						

						<p>It records the construction of a tank in memory of his ancestors, by Voḍla Pedavīranna of Vēlpucherla. It also states that Vīramma, wife of Peda Vīrabattu of Penikalapāḍu built a charity pond on the way to Vuppalūru and to the west of Vāmikoṇḍa.</p>						

						</summary>
